Pizza is a common experience in New York, even pizza slices this big seems to be a common occurrence these last few years. This Pizzeria has raised the bar, all the while being a tiny "mom and pop" place that your average consumer would just ignore. From the outside, and quite frankly the inside as well, the place looks like it hasn't had a facelift since before the turn of the century. And truly they don't matter, this isn't a sit-down establishment it a takeout place; which means all that matters is if the staff does their job well and above all else does their food taste good.  So the staff. Well, they seem nice! Considering all I do is stay what I want to throw money on the table and get my food and leave, with virtually no conversation why so ever, I think they are nice. On average I'm in and out in under 3 minutes no matter how much people I'm ordering for or how much people are in from of me that pretty damn good.  As for the food, this is the amazing part. The pizza is good. Like better than most pizza places I've been to. Maybe not the best but better than most and that saying things. This Pizzeria sales jumbo slices, basically pizza slices that are bigger than your head. I have never tasted a jumbo slice outside this pizzeria's that didn't lack flavor. It's the ultimate failure about the jumbo pizzas. They are large and cheap but 99.9% of the time lack qualities ingredients to make up for the cheap pricing. But this place makes them taste good. And yes they are affordable!
